                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00 Johnson Electoral Mission/197:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-26T11:00:00-05:45"
                            >May 26, 1931—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>87. I am awaiting a reply to my 74, May 22 [<hi rend="italic">12</hi>], 3 p.m.,
                    before taking up with President Moncada the designation of Major Price. I have
                    just learned that President Moncada is considering the appointment of Dr.
                    Aguado, the Vice President, as chairman of the National Board of Elections and
                    Dr. Aguado has expressed a desire to consult me in this matter. Please
                    instruct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
